item.description:
Waqas reports: Meta has disclosed a security incident involving an Instagram account recovery tool after attackers used a flaw to send password reset links to email addresses that were not connected to the targeted accounts. According to a data breach notice filed with the Maine Attorney General’s Office, Meta Platforms said the issue affected 20,225 people in...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F06%2F08%2Finstagram-recovery-tool-bug-exposed-20225-accounts-to-password-reset-abuse%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dinstagram-recovery-tool-bug-exposed-20225-accounts-to-password-reset-abuse&amp;action_name=Instagram%20Recovery%20Tool%20Bug%20Exposed%2020%2C225%20Accounts%20to%20Password%20Reset%20Abuse&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
<p><a href="https://databreaches.net/2026/06/08/instagram-recovery-tool-bug-exposed-20225-accounts-to-password-reset-abuse/?pk_campaign=feed&#038;pk_kwd=instagram-recovery-tool-bug-exposed-20225-accounts-to-password-reset-abuse">Source</a></p>

