Sergiu Gatlan reports: CISA has ordered U.S. government agencies to secure their Check Point Remote Access VPN and Mobile Access deployments against a critical vulnerability exploited in zero-day attacks by Qilin ransomware affiliates. Unauthenticated remote attackers can exploit this security flaw (tracked as CVE-2026-50751) to bypass authentication and establish a remote access VPN connection on targeted...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F06%2F09%2Fcisa-gives-feds-3-days-to-patch-check-point-vpn-bug-exploited-as-zero-day%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dcisa-gives-feds-3-days-to-patch-check-point-vpn-bug-exploited-as-zero-day&amp;action_name=CISA%20gives%20feds%203%20days%20to%20patch%20Check%20Point%20VPN%20bug%20exploited%20as%20zero-day&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
<p><a href="https://databreaches.net/2026/06/09/cisa-gives-feds-3-days-to-patch-check-point-vpn-bug-exploited-as-zero-day/?pk_campaign=feed&#038;pk_kwd=cisa-gives-feds-3-days-to-patch-check-point-vpn-bug-exploited-as-zero-day">Source</a></p>

